title: Plantable Seed Greeting Cards
product_description:
The perfect little token as a gift to a dear one or for yourself, these greeting cards feature pen and watercolor drawings of flora. Perfect for writing down intentions for growth , plant them in the ground and tend to your thoughts and hopes. Printed on plantable post-consumer paper, which is embedded with wildflower seeds containing Bird's Eye, Clarkia, Black Eye Susan, Sweet Alyssum, Catchfly, and Snapdragon.

How To Plant: Cover the card it with 1/8" of soil in full to partial sun and keep moist until the seeds establish. 

Details

  • Material: Paper / Seeds
  • Dimensions: A2 size 4 1/4" x 5 1/2"
  • Made in USA

title: Bosschaert Still Life Pocket Journal
product_description:
Beautiful and luxurious this journal combine high-quality production with magnificent art. The highly crafted covers are printed on foil paper, embossed then foil stamped, complemented by the luxury binding and rose red end-papers. These notebooks come with practical features too: a pocket at the back for scraps and receipts; two marigold ribbon markers to help keep track of more than just a to-do list; robust ivory text paper, printed with lines; and when you need to collect other notes or scraps of paper the magnetic side flap keeps everything neat and tidy.

Ambrosius Bosschaert the Elder was a Dutch Golden Age painter. The flowers in this arrangement, which include lilies, tulips, roses, and carnations, are painted with almost scientific precision. Bosschaert’s choice of a smooth copper support enhances the extraordinary detail of his brushwork.

  • 6"x4.5" / 176 Pages
